# Sources catalog

Curated sources for {{condition_name}} literature. Each entry has a purpose tag indicating how it should be used.

## Primary literature

- **PubMed** (NCBI) — primary index for biomedical literature. Search via the web UI at `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/`; round-trip via E-utilities (`https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/efetch.fcgi`). Source-of-truth for round-trip protocol per `meta/research-methodology.md`.
- **Semantic Scholar** — citation graph, useful for finding related and citing papers, and for older work that PubMed indexes patchily.
- **Cochrane Library** — systematic reviews and meta-analyses. Strongest evidence tier for treatment-effect questions.
- **ClinicalTrials.gov** — registered trials, including in-progress and unpublished. Useful for spotting publication bias.

